<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Container>
<Name>Transmission</Name>
<Description>
[b]Transmission bittorrent client under Slackware userspace[/b][br/]
[Transmission project page](www.transmissionbt.com)[br/]
Transmission is a BitTorrent client which features a simple interface on top of a cross-platform back-end. Transmission is free software licensed under the terms of the GNU General Public License (GPL), with parts under the MIT License.[br/]
[b]Directions:[/b][br/]
[b]Data Volumes:[/b][br/]
 * /srv/config : in this path Transmission will store it's configuration files.[br/]
 * /srv/downloads : in this path Transmission will store the downloaded files.[br/]
 * /srv/watchdir : in this path Transmission will wach for new torrents to download.[br/][br/]
[b]Network Ports:[/b][br/]
 * 9091 : Transmission rpc interface.[br/]
 * 64005 : Default BitTorrent communications port the Transmission uses.[br/]
 * 64000-64010 : Port range for Transmission to use.[br/]
</Description>
<Registry>https://registry.hub.docker.com/u/roninkenji/transmission-docker/</Registry>
<GitHub>https://github.com/roninkenji/transmission-docker</GitHub>
<Repository>roninkenji/transmission-docker</Repository>
<BindTime>true</BindTime>
<Privileged>false</Privileged>
